\n< Cecilia >Ah, damn it... my lower back hurts... what kind of
weight is that old man carrying...

\n< Cecilia >Well, with this, it's unlikely they'll find it for
a while. Those brats have been trained not to
enter the room on their own.
\n< Cecilia >How are you feeling?
\n< Serena >Somehow... the swelling on my face has gone down.
\n< Cecilia >Well, if that's the case, then it's fine...
\n< Serena >.......

\n< Cecilia >You have a gloomy face. Well, I mean, you just got
raped earlier, so it's not like you can be
cheerful.
\n< Serena >...That's... true but...
\n< Cecilia >What, are you concerned about someone dying? Ha.

\n< Cecilia >Got it? I already told you earlier, but you don't
have to worry about anything. That person is
someone who deserves to die, so I killed them.
\n< Cecilia >You just happened to be there at that moment.
\n< Cecilia >*sigh*..........
\n< Cecilia >Thanks for everything.
\n< Serena >Hmm...

\n< Cecilia >...I'll say it again, you don't have to worry
about anything.

\n< Cecilia >That person was living a life where it was only
natural for them to be stabbed from behind. They
died today because they weren't cautious enough. I
killed them.
\n< Cecilia >You just happened to be there at that moment.
\n< Cecilia >*sigh*..........

\n< Cecilia >Yes, yes. Anyway, this matter is already in my
hands. Finished. Switching topics. Let's get back
to the main point.
\n< Cecilia >Let's talk about what happens from now on.
\n< Serena >From now on?
\n< Cecilia >Yes. I...I owe you, Serena, a huge favor.
\n< Cecilia >So this time it's my turn.

\n< Cecilia >I will help Unicorn-chan. I will fully participate
in that plan.
\n< Serena >That... is appreciated, but...
\n< Serena >That... is sincerely appreciated.

\n< Cecilia >Especially now, in this situation. If used well,
it can greatly increase the accuracy of the plan.

\n< Cecilia >I just want some time to confirm things and
organize what needs to be done.

\n< Cecilia >I understand that Serena is in a hurry. So, please
give me just one night. I will gather and organize
the plan in one night.

\n< Cecilia >Come to the orphanage tomorrow when the sun rises.
I will talk to Serena about the plan there.

\n< Cecilia >You also need to rest your body and switch things
up. You need some time to calm down. Right now.
\n< Serena >...Hmm...
\n< Serena >Understood.
\n< Cecilia >Ah, and this. The money from earlier, 10,000 S.
\n< Serena >Ah...

\n< Cecilia >You're not planning to stay here overnight, are
you? Use it for the accommodation fee or
something.
\n< Serena >Let me do that...
\n< Serena >Let me do that.

\n< Cecilia >I think you understand, but the brats outside
still don't know what happened here.

\n< Cecilia >Make sure to leave naturally so as not to arouse
suspicion. If the situation here were to leak
outside, the plan would be ruined.
\n< Serena >Understood.
\n< Serena >Well then, tomorrow.
\n< Cecilia >Yeah, tomorrow.
\n< Serena >...Ugh...Ow...It hurts...
\n< Serena >.......

\n< Serena >...Let's leave behind all the fear, pain, guilt,
and confusion on this night.

\n< Serena >Finally, finally the path has opened. Now is not
the time to be kneeling...
\n< Serena >...It's completely night now.

\n< Serena >...Come to think of it, this might be the first
night I spend without anyone's orders since coming
to this town.
\n< Serena >.......

\n< Serena >...It's a little chilly. Let's quickly find an
inn.
